------------------------------------------------------------------------
SECTION 1: STATEMENT
------------------------------------------------------------------------

Theorem 4.1 (Fox 2026):
  Let C_120 be the 120-cell (120 dodecahedral cells, 600 vertices,
  1200 edges, 720 pentagonal faces). Each cell supports one route.
  Let H^2_fail be the sub-collection of modular curves X_0(N)
  for which the H2-fail criterion holds: Z > 10, route blocked.
  Then:

    N_routes = 120 - rank(H^2_fail) = 120 - 12 = 108.

Proof plan:
  A. h(-D) from first principles (quadratic form enumeration).
  B. CM_LIST parsed from M24 stdout (SHA-bound); h(-D) verified.
  C. PREDICT_FAIL parsed from M24 stdout (SHA-bound).
  D. Genus of each PREDICT_FAIL prime computed via Diamond-Shurman.
  E. M21 non-CM Hecke lift: genus >= 5 => Z >= 2g+1 >= 11 > 10.
  F. rank(H^2_fail) = 1 (CONFIRMED) + 11 (PREDICT) = 12.
  G. N_routes = 120 - 12 = 108.  QED.

