SECTION 5: GENUS VERIFICATION (DIAMOND-SHURMAN THM 3.1.1)
------------------------------------------------------------------------

For odd prime p >= 5 (Diamond-Shurman Theorem 3.1.1):
  eps2 = 1 + Leg(-1,p)  [0 if p=3 mod 4; 2 if p=1 mod 4]
  eps3 = 1 + Leg(-3,p)  [0 if p=2 mod 3; 2 if p=1 mod 3]
  12*g = (p+1) - 3*eps2 - 4*eps3   [exact integer arithmetic]

      N   p%4   p%3   eps2   eps3   genus g   Z_min=2g+1  g>=5?
     67     3     1      0      2         5           11  YES
     73     1     1      2      2         5           11  YES
    103     3     1      0      2         8           17  YES
    107     3     2      0      0         9           19  YES
    167     3     2      0      0        14           29  YES
    191     3     2      0      0        16           33  YES
    193     1     1      2      2        15           31  YES
    223     3     1      0      2        18           37  YES
    227     3     2      0      0        19           39  YES
    229     1     1      2      2        18           37  YES
    269     1     2      2      0        22           45  YES

All 11 PREDICT_FAIL primes have genus >= 5  [VERIFIED]

